source.name: Pedestrian High-Injury Corridors, San Francisco, CA
source.description: High-injury corridors represent 5.2% of San Francisco’s street miles, and include 55% of all severe and fatal injuries and 51% of total pedestrian injuries reported to the State Highway Patrol between 2005 and 2009.
